FBIS4-63901 "drsov102_b_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-102 Daily Report 26 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Federal Counterintelligence Service Heads Meet Federal Counterintelligence Service Heads Meet LD2605091494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0757 GMT 26 May 94 LD2605091494 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By KRIM-TASS correspondent Olga Semenova] [Text] Moscow May 26 TASS -- Heads of departments and regional bodies of the Federal Counter-intelligence Service met in Moscow today to attend a two-day all-Russia conference on problems of fighting organised crime, terrorism and drug business. The conference is being attended by representatives from the Russian Interior Ministry, the prosecutor's office and other law enforcement bodies and secret services since problems put on the agenda require close interaction between these structures. The conference will be addressed by Russian President Boris Yeltsin who will assess the work carried out by the federal counter- intelligence service and outline new tasks in the area of the activities of the counter-intelligence service.
